      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ يَجْعَلُ عَلَيْهِ صِيَاماً فِي نَذْرٍ فَلاَ يَقْوَى قَالَ \"يُعْطِي مَنْ يَصُومُ عَنْهُ كُلَّ يَوْمٍ مُدَّيْنِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4314 - Abdullah ibn Jabalah narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar, from Abu Abdillah (as), regarding a man who makes fasting obligatory upon himself through a vow but is unable to fulfill it.\nImam (as) said: \"He should give two mudds of food for each day to someone who will fast on his behalf.\""
        ]
      }
